.SH SHCilmToVector
Convert a three\-dimensional array of real spherical harmonic
coefficients to a 1\-dimensional indexed vector.
.SH Usage
call SHCilmToVector (\f[CR]cilm\f[R], \f[CR]vector\f[R],
\f[CR]lmax\f[R], \f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]cilm\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)
The input real spherical harmonic coefficients.
.TP
\f[CR]vector\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension ( (\f[CR]lmax\f[R]+1)**2 )
The indexed output real spherical harmonic coefficients.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The maximum degree of the output coefficients to convert.
.TP
\f[CR]exitstatus\f[R] : output, optional, integer(int32)
If present, instead of executing a STOP when an error is encountered,
the variable exitstatus will be returned describing the error.
0 = No errors; 1 = Improper dimensions of input array; 2 = Improper
bounds for input variable; 3 = Error allocating memory; 4 = File IO
error.
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHCilmToVector\f[R] will convert a three\-dimensional array of
real spherical harmonic coefficients to a 1\-dimensional indexed array.
The degree \f[CR]l\f[R], order \f[CR]m\f[R], and \f[CR]i\f[R] (1 for
cosine, 2 for sine) corresponds to the index
\f[CR]l**2+(i\-1)*l+m+1\f[R].
